OL,3,CMother's fight to reopen the case of
OL,4,Cher son's death
OL,6,FAccording to former police officer
OL,7,FCarwyn Evans, who lectures at the
OL,8,FUniversity of South Wales, collisions
OL,9,Finvolving pedestrians "do not always
OL,10,Flead to prosecution."
OL,12,FHe said: "A lot of accidents like this
OL,13,Ftake place in the middle of the night,
OL,14,Fwhere there aren't many witnesses
OL,15,Faround, maybe no CCTV, and it can be
OL,16,Fhard to work out what has happened."
